@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About</PageTitle>

<div class="about-container">
    <h1>About the App</h1>

    <section class="about-section">
        <p>
            Welcome to <strong>Due Performance (DP) Calculator</strong> — a productivity tool designed to help students monitor and plan their academic progress throughout the semester.
        </p>
        <p>
            Whether you're tracking assessments, setting goals, or aiming for a passing average, this app gives you clarity and control over your academic journey.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Set a target DP and track your current academic performance.</li>
            <li>Log and manage individual assessments for each module.</li>
            <li>Instantly see whether you're passing or need to take action.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h2>How to Use</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to the <strong>DP Tracker</strong> page and add your modules.</li>
            <li>For each module, set your target average (e.g., 50%).</li>
            <li>Add all your assessments (even if you haven't written them yet) for the semester with their respective weighted marks.</li>
            <li>Ensure your weighted marks all equal to <strong>100%</strong> to get accurate calculations.</li>
            <li>As you complete assessments, update their scores in the app.</li>
            <li>As you update your scores, the app will automatically calculate your current average and tell you whether you're on track.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            Use this app regularly to stay ahead and make informed decisions about your studies!
        </p>
    </section>
</div>


